  "prompt": "How do you activate Facetime on the iPhone?",
  "response": "To activate FaceTime on an iPhone:\n\n1. Open the Settings app\n2. Scroll down and tap on \"FaceTime\"\n3. Toggle the FaceTime switch to turn it on\n4. Sign in with your Apple ID (if not already signed in)\n5. Decide whether you want to be reached by phone number, email, or both\n\nOnce activated, you can make a FaceTime call by:\n- Tapping the FaceTime app\n- Opening Contacts and tapping the FaceTime icon\n- Using the Phone app and selecting FaceTime\n- Asking Siri to \"FaceTime\" a contact\n\nNote: You'll need a Wi-Fi or cellular data connection to use FaceTime.",
